The article is a transcript of a briefing by White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs. He gives a readout of President Obama's meeting on Afghanistan and Pakistan, highlighting the progress made in building a strong partnership with Pakistan and the leading role of the Afghan government and security forces in the current offensive. He also discusses the capture of Mullah Baradar, the number two Afghan Taliban, and the success of the Recovery Act in creating jobs and economic growth. Gibbs addresses criticism of the stimulus package and emphasizes the need for bipartisan cooperation in solving economic problems. He also mentions upcoming meetings with the Dalai Lama and General Odierno, as well as the establishment of a debt commission. Finally, he responds to questions about the progress of the offensive in southern Afghanistan and the allocation of funds from the stimulus package.